{
  "stem": "15732.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my father immediately started to think how he is going to organize.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He's going to open a tailor shop and so on, so forth.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I felt it's no good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm just going to finish my life in Beuthen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As young as I was, I felt that a conclusion or a lesson must be learned from what we went through.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No more Romania, no more Russia, no more Poland, no more anything.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "All I wanted is to go to Palestine, to be among my own people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No more chasing, no more running, no more escaping.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] well, I felt that is what I have to look into.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And as it so happened, two or three weeks after we were in Beuthen, we heard rumors-- Jews like to talk-- that there are people who organized the so-called Berihah.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[HEBREW] in Hebrew means to escape.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was a organization-- there was a group, not organization I should call-- a group called that were organized from the Jewish Brigade, which was at that time in Europe.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "What they really wanted was helping all those that come from camps from there and don't have a home and don't have parents or-- or children-- there were thousands and thousands of orphans, young orphans, to give them a home to organize them they should come over to Palestine, not-- to come certainly to Palestine, you can't go because it's was English mandate.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But what we wanted to aim to was to organize the so-called Aliyah Bet.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "That means the illegal Aliyah to Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We made his contact with-- there turned out to be a very young chap, maybe 20 or 21, very young, who said, you know what?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I can smuggle you over to Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
